<HEADLINE> Jeep Crashes Into Pool Hall  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   LOS ANGELES (AP) -- A sport utility vehicle crashed into a
crowded pool hall near the UCLA campus Wednesday night, killing one
person and injuring at least eight others.
</P>
<P>
   Witnesses said the driver was slumped over the wheel as the
vehicle rear-ended another car at a nearby intersection, then
accelerated rapidly, shoving the car aside, hitting a tree and
roaring over the curb and into the front of Q's Billiard Club.
</P>
<P>
   When the vehicle finally stopped, it was entirely inside the
pool hall's front bar and restaurant area, and the floor was
covered with shattered glass and splintered wood.
</P>
<P>
   A man on the sidewalk outside the pool hall died after the
vehicle hit him, Sgt. Steve Foster said. At least two other men
inside the pool hall were critically injured.
</P>
<P>
   The driver was taken to UCLA Medical Center, where police were
waiting to speak with him, Foster said.
</P>
<P>
   ''It's unknown at this point if he was intoxicated or if there
was a medical condition,'' Foster said. ''It could have been almost
anything. It's hard to say.''
</P>
</TEXT>
