<HEADLINE> Hiding Suspect Crushed in Compacter  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   DETROIT (AP) -- A woman suspected of shoplifting was crushed to
death Wednesday when she tried to hide in a garbage compactor after
fleeing security, police said.
</P>
<P>
   Guards at a Value Village store had detained her after
suspecting her of shoplifting, but the woman ran, Officer Glen
Woods said.
</P>
<P>
   ''I guess the first place she ran to hide was the compactor,''
Woods said.
</P>
<P>
   Woods said the woman, identified as Gloria Terrell, 43, was
crushed to death after workers who were putting items into the
compactor started the machine. They had been on a break when the
woman apparently went inside the machine and didn't notice she was
there until they restarted it.
</P>
<P>
   ''The police told me she stole a pair of shoes,'' Terrell's
mother, Shirley Terrell, told the Detroit Free Press. ''For her to
lose her life for a pair of shoes ... I don't know what to say.''
</P>
</TEXT>
