<HEADLINE> Ramirez Headed for DL  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   CLEVELAND (AP) -- All-Star right fielder Manny Ramirez, sidelined
with a strained left hamstring muscle became the latest Cleveland
Indians player to go on the 15-day disabled list.
</P>
<P>
   The Indians also said Wednesday night that left-hander Ricardo
Rincon will have surgery to remove bone spurs in his elbow and
could be out the remainder of the season.
</P>
<P>
   Cleveland didn't announce the planned move of Ramirez or
Rincon's surgery until after its 7-3 victory over the Anaheim
Angels.
</P>
<P>
   Ramirez, who leads the Indians with 47 RBIs, got hurt while
running out a ground ball during Monday's game against the Chicago
White Sox. He was unavailable the past two games, and will be
officially added to Cleveland's crowded DL on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
   The Indians have eight players -- six pitchers -- on the DL and
have made 23 player transactions since May 18.
</P>
<P>
   To take Ramirez's spot, the Indians will recall right-hander
Jamie Brewington from Triple-A Buffalo. The 28-year-old was 1-0
with a 3.18 ERA in 22 2-3 innings for the Bisons.
</P>
<P>
   Rincon, placed on the DL on May 18, still felt pain in his elbow
while throwing a 60-pitch simulated game on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
   ''I told Charlie it still hurts when I throw my slider,'' Rincon
said.
</P>
<P>
   Manuel said Rincon, who received a cortisone shot last week,
said the surgery will be performed by Dr. James Andrews in
Birmingham, Ala. No date has been set for the procedure.
</P>
</TEXT>
