   With Vodichkova hitting from the perimeter, the Storm rallied
from a seven-point halftime deficit, tying the game at 46 on an
outside shot by Campbell.
</P>
<P>
   Sacramento answered right back, with Steding hitting a 3-pointer
and Clinesmith making another to give the Monarchs a 52-46
advantage with 9:56 remaining.
</P>
<P>
   Holland-Corn made three 3-pointers and had 10 points as the
Monarchs overcame an early deficit to take a 36-29 halftime lead.
</P>
<P>
   Byears scored eight first-half points for the Monarchs, who went
unbeaten in four preseason games.
