<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Dodgers 4, Mets 3  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   LOS ANGELES (AP) -- Kevin Elster homered in the ninth inning and
Chad Kreuter also connected as the Los Angeles Dodgers beat the New
York Mets 4-3 Wednesday night in a game overshadowed by injuries to
Mike Piazza and Kevin Brown.
</P>
<P>
   Turk Wendell (4-3) relieved to start the ninth and Elster
homered against his former team for the first time, lining the ball
into the left-field bullpen.
</P>
<P>
   Reliever Mike Fetters (2-0) retired two batters in the top on
the ninth.
</P>
<P>
   Piazza was knocked out of the game in the sixth when Gary
Sheffield's bat hit him on the follow-through. The seven-time
All-Star catcher sustained a slight concussion and a gash on his
forehead that required one stitch.
</P>
<P>
   The Mets said Piazza should be back in the lineup Friday when
the team returns home to play Tampa Bay.
</P>
<P>
   Brown was hit by a liner off the bat of Edgardo Alfonzo and left
after six innings because of a bruised right leg. The ball was hit
so hard that it ricocheted into foul territory.
</P>
<P>
   Brown chased the ball down just outside the first-base line,
grabbed it with his bare hand and in the same motion whipped an
accurate sidearm throw to first base for the out -- while flying
toward the dugout and stumbling to regain his balance.
</P>
<P>
   Brown allowed one run and three hits and struck out five. His
injury occurred just hours after the Dodgers placed catcher Todd
Hundley on the 15-day disabled list because of a strained abdominal
oblique muscle in his right rib cage.
</P>
<P>
   Kreuter's homer and RBI singles by Shawn Green and Eric Karros
gave the Dodgers a 3-1 lead against Mike Hampton.
</P>
<P>
   But the Mets tied it with two in the eighth against Alan Mills.
Kurt Abbott led off with his first homer of the season and Alfonzo,
who homered and had two RBIs, drove in pinch-runner Jon Nunnelly
with a double off the short fence in the right-field corner.
</P>
<P>
   Hampton gave up two earned runs and five hits in seven innings.
</P>
<P>
Notes: Brown was on the 15-day disabled list earlier this season
after breaking his finger attempting to bunt at Shea Stadium. ...
Hundley became the fourth Dodgers' regular to hit the DL this
season, joining CF Devon White, SS Elster and 3B Adrian Beltre. ...
Hampton got his ninth hit of the season on a dribbler up the
third-base line in the fifth. ... Los Angeles manager Davey Johnson
said he will give closer Jeff Shaw a few days off. Shaw, who blew a
save for the fifth time Tuesday night, has been pitching for two
weeks with a knot behind his right shoulder. ... Alfonzo has five
homers in 11 games.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
