<HEADLINE> Clinton Sending Albright To Mideast  </HEADLINE>
By TOM RAUM
<TEXT>
<P>
   LISBON, Portugal (AP) -- President Clinton said today he is
sending Secretary of State Madeleine Albright to the Middle East to
narrow the gaps in the peace process between Israel and the
Palestinians. He said both sides ''have to be prepared to make an
intense effort and to do things that they have not done in the
past.''
</P>
<P>
   He said it would require ''real courage and vision'' to achieve
a framework agreement on the major differences between them.
</P>
<P>
   He spoke after meeting with Israeli Prime Minister Ehud Barak
and said he would meet soon in Washington with Palestinian leader
Yasser Arafat.
</P>
</TEXT>
