<HEADLINE> Truck slams into parked trailer, killing driver  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	   LE ROY, N.Y. (AP) -- A truck slammed into an unoccupied
tractor-trailer parked on the side of the New York state Thruway,
killing the driver, spilling a hazardous cargo and backing up
rush-hour traffic for miles Thursday.
</P>
<P>
   The tractor-trailer had pulled off the highway after striking a
deer and the driver apparently had walked off to seek help, state
police said. A truck crashed into its rear around 8 a.m. some eight
miles west of the Le Roy exit and 25 miles southwest of Rochester.
</P>
<P>
   Killed was Joseph Price III, 49, of Long Pond, Pa.
</P>
<P>
   Firefighters were summoned to contain chlorine that spilled
along with diesel fuel from the wreckage of the parked truck.
</P>
<P>
   ''We have to contain it as soon as possible and keep it away
from the diesel, which will cause it to explode,'' Batavia Fire
Chief Frank Riccobone told the Daily News of Batavia.
</P>
<P>
   Westbound lanes of the highway were closed for about five hours.
</P>
</TEXT>
