<HEADLINE> Woo Comforted Cruise Mom Over Scene  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   HONG KONG (AP) -- Director John Woo had a mission to comfort Tom
Cruise's mother when he sent his leading man up a cliff for a
dizzying climbing scene. It turned out to be mission impossible.
</P>
<P>
   ''She's finally calming down and she's trying to pretend she's
not scared, so she kept smiling at me,'' as they watched the
''Mission Impossible 2'' star climb an overhanging cliff some 2,000
feet above ground without a safety net, Woo said.
</P>
<P>
   ''But I was more panicked then her, so I grabbed hold of her
hand, turned to her, and said, 'Mom, he's going to be fine,' and
actually I was the one worried,'' Woo recalled.
</P>
<P>
   Cruise did that stunt seven times, and his mother and Woo
''worried 70 times,'' the director told reporters in Hong Kong. ''I
kept sweating. I closed my eyes and prayed to God.''
</P>
<P>
   The Hong Kong director came home with Cruise to promote the
action-packed sequel to the 1996 blockbuster.
</P>
<P>
   Cruise insisted on doing all the stunts, said Woo, who made his
name making shoot-'em-up Hong Kong gangster movies before going to
Hollywood.
</P>
<P>
   ''The film is his babe, and he wanted to do the best,'' Woo
said.
</P>
<P>
   Cruise, on his second trip here, said he looks forward to
working with Woo again.
</P>
<P>
   ''He takes action and elevates beyond the way that we knew
before,'' Cruise said.
</P>
</TEXT>
