<HEADLINE> Big Movers in the Stock Market  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW YORK (AP) -- Stocks that moved substantially or traded
heavily Thursday on the New York Stock Exchange and Nasdaq Stock
Market.
</P>
<P>
NYSE
</P>
<P>
Hewlett-Packard Co., up $14.375 at $134.50
</P>
<P>
   Banc of America Securities analyst Kurtis King upgraded the
stock to ''strong buy'' from ''buy'' following the company's
semiannual meeting with analysts. King cited strength in the
computer server business and the leadership of chief executive
Carly Fiorina.
</P>
<P>
Pfizer Inc., up 68.8 cents at $45.25
</P>
<P>
   Merrill Lynch analyst Steven Tighe added Pfizer to Merrill's
''Focus 1'' list, telling clients Pfizer is the ''best-positioned
pharmaceutical company in the industry.'' Also, a Pfizer-funded
study found that the impotence-treatment drug Viagra does not cause
adverse effects in users with heart disease.
</P>
<P>
Abercrombie &AMP; Fitch Co., down $1.125 at $8.688
</P>
<P>
   The retailer said same-store sales fell 14 percent in May. For
the year to date, same-store sales fell 9 percent. Sales from
stores open at least a year, known as same-store sales, are
considered the most accurate measure of a retailer's business.
</P>
<P>
NASDAQ
</P>
<P>
Pacific Sunwear of California Inc., down $3.625 at $12.438
</P>
<P>
   The company warned that second-quarter earnings may fall below
analysts' estimates if June and July same-store sales increase by
less than 6 percent, or if merchandise profit margins are hurt. In
May, same-store sales rose just 0.5 percent.
</P>
<P>
UTStarcom Inc., down $17.563 at $20.688
</P>
<P>
   The telecommunications equipment provider said installation of
its products is under review by the Chinese Ministry of Information
Industry. During the review period, expected to be about 60 days,
UTStarcom was requested to temporarily halt new deployments of its
PAS wireless telephone access system.
</P>
<P>
Matritech Inc., up $3.094 at $7.531
</P>
<P>
   The company said its NMP66 test was successful in the company's
early testing. The NMP66 is a blood test for women with breast
cancer or who may run the risk of breast cancer; Matritech said the
preliminary test detected every case.
</P>
<P>
Gemstar International Group Ltd., up $4.75 at $47.188
</P>
<P>
   The company earned 11 cents per share in its recently ended
fourth quarter, up from 9 cents per share a year earlier. The
results included charges for the acquisition of NuvoMedia and
SoftBook Press; without those charges, Gemstar would have earned 17
cents per share.
</P>
</TEXT>
