<HEADLINE> Lakers' Bryant Probable for Game 6  </HEADLINE>
By JOHN NADEL
<TEXT>
<P>
   EL SEGUNDO, Calif. (AP) -- Kobe Bryant missed practice Thursday
because of his sprained right foot, and his availability for Game 6
of the Western Conference finals is in question.
</P>
<P>
   Los Angeles Lakers spokesman John Black listed Bryant, an
All-NBA second team selection, as probable, but said a decision
wouldn't be made until tipoff Friday night.
</P>
<P>
   Lakers coach Phil Jackson wasn't so sure, and Bryant didn't
speak with reporters before the team flew to Portland.
</P>
<P>
   ''He's not ready to practice yet,'' Jackson said. ''We don't
know. We'll know game-time about that.''
</P>
<P>
   Bryant sprained his foot early in Tuesday night's 96-88 loss to
the Trail Blazers at Staples Center that trimmed the Lakers' lead
in the best-of-seven series to 3-2 and forced a sixth game.
</P>
<P>
   Bryant played on, and not very well, especially compared to what
he did during the regular season and earlier in the playoffs.
X-rays following the game showed no fracture, and further X-rays
and an MRI on Wednesday were negative.
</P>
<P>
   ''We're not really sure right now if Kobe can play,'' backup
guard Derek Fisher said. ''If Kobe can play, he'll play. I expect
him to at least go out there and give it a shot. I don't know how
much pain he is in.
</P>
<P>
   ''If his foot isn't amputated, I expect him to give it a go.
Eighty-to-85 percent of Kobe Bryant is a lot better than a lot of
people.''
</P>
<P>
   Bryant is averaging 17.0 points, 4.2 rebounds and 5.6 assists in
the conference finals, and 21.9 points, 4.1 rebounds and 4.2
assists in 15 playoff games.
</P>
<P>
   ''I know he'll be out there,'' reserve forward Robert Horry
said. ''It's the most important game of his career, so far. He'll
be out there.''
</P>
<P>
   As for the possibility of Bryant playing and being slowed by the
injury, Horry said, ''It might be a blessing in disguise, he won't
be able to run around so much.''
</P>
<P>
   Bryant committed six of the Lakers' 16 turnovers in Game 5,
prompting Jackson to say he played out of control at times.
</P>
<P>
   Lakers forward Glen Rice said he believes Bryant will be limited
if he plays.
</P>
<P>
   ''Myself and everybody's going to have to pick up their game,''
Rice said. ''We realize he does have an injury. As a group, we have
to band together and be strong.''
</P>
<P>
   Bryant worked out lightly Wednesday, and might very well have
tried to do more had Jackson not ordered him to the sidelines. He
was dressed in practice gear Thursday, but didn't work out, instead
receiving treatment.
</P>
<P>
   Bryant had said Wednesday he expected to be better Thursday and,
when asked if he'd be ready Friday night, replied, ''Oh,
absolutely.''
</P>
<P>
   He also said his sprained foot was no factor in his sub-par
performance in Game 5.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
