<DOCNO> APW20000601.0183 </DOCNO>
<DOCTYPE> NEWS STORY </DOCTYPE>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-06-01 20:28 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Gunmen Open Fire on Belize Boat  </HEADLINE>
By KARLA HEUSNER
<TEXT>
<P>
   BELIZE CITY, Belize (AP) -- Halfway through a commuter boat ride,
three crew members suddenly opened fire on the captain and
passengers, killing at least five people and throwing surviving
women and children overboard, authorities said Thursday.
</P>
<P>
   Three survivors said they spent 17 hours floating together in
the Gulf of Honduras until a fisherman discovered them Wednesday
morning. Others drowned one by one as they waited for rescue.
</P>
<P>
   ''They just opened fire like nothing, like crazy. They just
shot,'' said 21-year-old passenger Evelyn Rojas, describing the
assault Tuesday on the boat ''Maria Estela,'' which had been taking
passengers from Guatemala to Belize.
</P>
<P>
   There was no known motive for the attack.
</P>
<P>
   Carrying 10 passengers and a crew of five, the 28-foot skiff
left Guatemala's Puerto Barrios on Tuesday afternoon for the
normally uneventful trip through the Gulf of Honduras in the
Caribbean Sea to Belize's Punta Gorda.
</P>
<P>
   Less than an hour into the voyage, as the light craft neared
Guatemala's maritime border, the three mutineers grabbed assault
weapons they had hidden under boxes and turned them on the
passengers, authorities and survivors said.
</P>
<P>
   Five passengers apparently were shot dead immediately,
Guatemalan Naval Capt. Jose Maria Valladres said Thursday.
</P>
<P>
   Rojas said she jumped into the water and tried to swim as far
from the boat as possible, grabbing a life jacket and hanging on
amid a shower of bullets.
</P>
<P>
   The assailants, meanwhile, shot other passengers and threw
women, children and an elderly man overboard, she said.
</P>
<P>
   The captain, Julio Requena Jr., jumped into the water after
being shot, but the gunmen continued to fire on him in the water,
said passenger Larry Smith, an American who has lived in Belize for
27 years.
</P>
<P>
   Although Requena managed to avoid being shot again, not long
after the assault ended he ''told us goodbye and disappeared into
the water,'' Smith said.
</P>
<P>
   Late Wednesday, a Belizean tour cruiser recovered the bodies of
two Belizeans, a Honduran man and two Guatemalans, all of whom had
been shot.
</P>
<P>
   Aside from the three passengers who were rescued, the others
aboard had not been accounted for, and authorities said some may be
hostages aboard the boat, which was still missing. Belizean naval
boats were searching for the assailants.
</P>
<P>
   Although Guatemala and Belize have been locked in a border
dispute since January, both sides agreed the attack was not
politically motivated.
</P>
<P>
   ------
</P>
<P>
   EDITOR'S NOTE -- Associated Press Writer Will Weissert in
Guatemala City contributed to this report.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER> AP-NY-06-01-00 2028 </TRAILER>
</DOC>
