<TEXT>
<P>
 Thursday, June 1, 2000
</P>
<SUBHEAD>
Elian's Dad Makes Plea To Relatives
</SUBHEAD>
<P>
   WASHINGTON (AP) -- Juan Miguel Gonzalez asked his Miami relatives today to
end their court battle to keep 6-year-old Elian in this country and allow father
and son to ''finally go back home together'' to Cuba. Speaking hours after the
11th Circuit Court of Appeals sided with him in the 6-month-long custody battle,
Gonzalez said, ''A child simply should be with his parents, always with his
parents. As the father, I should be speaking on behalf of my son.'' In its
ruling, the three-judge panel said the Immigration and Naturalization Service's
decision that only a parent can act for a 6-year-old child in immigration
matters was reasonable.
</P>
<SUBHEAD>
Bush Grants Death Row Reprieve
</SUBHEAD>
<P>
   HUNTSVILLE, Texas (AP) -- With less than a half-hour before a convicted
killer's scheduled execution tonight, George W. Bush approved his first reprieve
in a Texas death penalty case. Bush issued a 30-day reprieve for Ricky McGinn
who was set to die for killing his 12-year-old stepdaughter seven years ago.
Bush has allowed 131 lethal injections over his 5{ years as governor of the
nation's busiest execution state.
</P>
<SUBHEAD>
Russia Targets Chechnya's Mountains
</SUBHEAD>
<P>
   GUDERMES, Russia (AP) -- Russian forces pounded Chechnya's mountains with
warplanes and artillery Thursday, trying to drive hundreds of rebels out of
their strongholds, the military said. Russian officials in Chechnya also claimed
that Aslan Maskhadov, the elected president of Chechnya, had been wounded in the
most recent fighting. Maskhadov was wounded overnight outside the village of
Malye Shuani in the Nozhai-Yurt region, where Russian forces have directed much
of their bombing and shelling, said a spokesman in Gudermes, Chechnya's
second-largest city, which is under Russian control.
</P>
