Columbine Sheriff Recall Plan Starts
</SUBHEAD>
<P>
   GOLDEN, Colo. (AP) -- The families of three Columbine students launched a
drive today to recall Jefferson County Sheriff John Stone, whom they accuse of
mishandling the law enforcement response to last year's massacre at the high
school and the investigation into it. ''Sheriff Stone should resign,'' said
Brian Rohrbaugh, whose son, Daniel, was one of the 12 students killed by Eric
Harris and Dylan Klebold. ''It would be the one decent thing in his career he
could do to serve the public.''
</P>
<SUBHEAD>
Date Set For Fiji Hostages Release
</SUBHEAD>
<P>
   SUVA, Fiji (AP) -- Rebels holding more than 30 hostages in Fiji's parliament
plan to release them over the weekend, the leader of the armed group said
Friday. George Speight announced the plan at a news conference just prior to a
meeting with the country's new military leader to discuss the hostages' fate.
Speight said the hostages -- who include deposed Prime Minister Mahendra
Chaudhry, the first ethnic Indian to be elected to that position -- would be
freed before the a meeting on Monday of Fiji's influential Great Council of
Chiefs.
</P>
<SUBHEAD>
