sprained right foot, and his availability for Game 6 of the Western Conference
finals is in question. Los Angeles Lakers spokesman John Black listed Bryant, an
All-NBA second team selection, as probable, but said a decision wouldn't be made
until tipoff tomorrow night. Lakers coach Phil Jackson wasn't so sure, and
Bryant didn't speak with reporters before the team flew to Portland.
</P>
