<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Miracle 82, Sting 79  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   ORLANDO, Fla. (AP) -- Nykesha Sales scored 24 points and the
Orlando Miracle held off a late charge by the Charlotte Sting to
win their home opener 82-79 Thursday night.
</P>
<P>
   Shannon Johnson added 16 points, Adrienne Johnson 14 and Taj
McWilliams 11 for Orlando.
</P>
<P>
   Charlotte cut Orlando's lead to 80-79 on a layup and foul shot
by Rhonda Mapp with 33.5 seconds remaining. Shannon Johnson was
fouled and hit both free throws for the final margin. Charlotte
Smith's game-tying 3-point attempt was short.
</P>
<P>
   Andrea Stinson led Charlotte with 18. Smith added 15 and Mapp 10
for the Sting, who shot 7-of-14 from 3-point range.
</P>
<P>
   Orlando led by as many as 13 in the second half, 70-57, at the
9:37 mark.
</P>
<P>
   Charlotte got to 76-71 with 2:52 remaining on a 3-pointer by
Smith. The teams traded baskets until Stinson's 3-pointer cut
Orlando's lead to 80-76 with 1:40 left.
</P>
<P>
   McWilliams' jumper at the 6:19 mark in the first half broke a
25-25 tie as the Miracle went on a 17-6 run to take a 42-31 lead
with 1:47 remaining.
</P>
<P>
   Charlotte closed with a 6-2 run to trail 44-37 at the half.
Sales led all scorers with 18 first-half points on 6-of-13
shooting.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER> AP-NY-06-01-00 2229 </TRAILER>
