<HEADLINE> Fever 57, Sol 54  </HEADLINE>
By MARK LONG
<TEXT>
<P>
   MIAMI (AP) -- Kara Wolters, outplayed for much of the game,
scored six of her eight points in the final six minutes as the
Indiana Fever beat the Miami Sol 57-54 Thursday night in both
teams' opening game of their inaugural seasons.
</P>
<P>
   The Fever overcame a 17-point second-half deficit, and Wolters
added a key block in the closing seconds for the victory.
</P>
<P>
   Indiana trailed 39-22 early in the second half, but used a 30-11
run to take a 52-50 lead with about two minutes to play.
</P>
<P>
   The 6-foot-7 Wolters hit two short jumpers, and Rita Williams
followed with a 3-pointer to give the Fever their first lead.
</P>
<P>
   Williams and Wolters added back-to-back baskets with a little
more than a minute remaining to seal the victory. Wolters also
blocked Jameka Jones' baseline runner in the final minute.
</P>
<P>
   The Sol had a chance to tie with three seconds to play, but
couldn't get off a shot. Miami shot 30 percent and made just eight
baskets in the second half. Indiana shot 46 percent.
</P>
<P>
   Wolters had been outmatched for much of the game by Miami center
Marlies Askamp, who had 13 points and 10 rebounds and dominated the
lane. Debbie Black, the Sol's scrappy on-court leader, added 13
points and four assists.
</P>
<P>
   Wolters was quiet for much of the night as she settled for jump
hooks, badly missing most of the time.
</P>
<P>
   With little help from Wolters and teammate Stephanie McCarty,
the Fever cut into the lead in the second half.
</P>
<P>
   Much of the spurt came without forward Jurgita Streimikyte. She
left the game at the 12:17 mark with a sprained right ankle. She
had to be helped off the court after scoring six points.
</P>
<P>
   Moments later, she headed to the locker room. She returned with
a splint and crutches.
</P>
<P>
   The Fever didn't score in the final 6:45 of the first half. But
the Sol also struggled to find the basket, missing an opportunity
to pull away.
</P>
<P>
   Miami used a 12-2 run to take a 23-12 lead early.
</P>
<P>
   Alicia Thompson, who led the Fever with 13 points, hit a jumper
with just under seven minutes to play to cut the lead to 27-20, but
Indiana didn't score again. The Sol's final six first-half points
came from the free-throw line.
</P>
<P>
   They got a lot of help on the boards, too. On four straight
possessions, Miami missed a second free throw, but got the
offensive rebound and converted it into points.
</P>
<P>
   The Sol outrebounded the Fever 21-13 in the first half,
including 13-3 on the offensive end. They led 33-20 at the break.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
